1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:26,080
I'd like to formally
welcome you to Paisal Farm,

2
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:27,680
my beautiful soon-to-be sister-in-law!

3
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,520
- Whoa.
- Na.

4
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:32,160
On?

5
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,080
I'm appointing Pin to lead

6
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:39,280
the Accounting and Finance Department
of Paisal Farm.

7
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:42,120
Pinanong was an accomplice
in extorting money from Paisal Farm.

8
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:43,840
Pin might have gotten away,

9
00:02:43,920 --> 00:02:45,800
but don't think you'll walk free.

10
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:48,240
I'll send all of you to prison!

11
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:49,840
Thank you so much.

12
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:53,480
If they come again,
tell them I'm on leave for several days.

13
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:04,880
As expected.

14
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:09,080
Mr. Yai went to my office,
and Jom went to my house.

15
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:12,400
We were right to come here.

16
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:14,760
I told the Subdistrict Head

17
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:17,280
that I'll have a friend
come stay here for a few days.

18
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:18,960
You're okay now.

19
00:03:19,680 --> 00:03:22,720
Jin, I'm sorry for troubling you.

20
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:23,960
Pin.

21
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,440
Do you think you did the right thing?

22
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:30,600
It's true that you love your mom,

23
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:32,480
and you always obey her.

24
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:37,080
But Pin, wrongdoers must be punished.

25
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:41,040
You shouldn't treat that
as if it were Madam's personal money.

26
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:46,040
Don't forget that it's Mr. Yai's farm.

27
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:50,000
I know.

28
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:53,520
But I have no choice.

29
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,000
I couldn't manage our finances well,

30
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,000
so I had no choice but to try gambling

31
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:03,280
to earn some money,
so I could send it to Na.

32
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:07,160
That doesn't even include
the money to solve Nee's problems.

33
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:11,080
You already know

34
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:13,120
there was a pandemic,

35
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:16,279
and the farm had no income.

36
00:04:17,440 --> 00:04:19,399
I didn't know what I was supposed to do.

37
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:22,840
I'm sorry. I'm sorry…

38
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:24,440
Madam.

39
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:28,240
I understand you. I know how you feel.

40
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,400
You don't need to feel guilty.

41
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:31,800
Don't apologize.

42
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:33,960
This is not your fault, Madam.

43
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:38,240
But you shouldn't have resorted
to gambling.

44
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:47,040
Pin! What do you know about that?

45
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:49,680
You've been educated, well-fed,
and live a comfortable life now

46
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:51,840
because of all the money Madam has earned!

47
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:53,800
Pin.

48
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:58,280
I'm not afraid to go to prison alone.

49
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:01,360
But I feel bad for Na.

50
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:04,440
He must be so disappointed

51
00:05:04,520 --> 00:05:07,120
and ashamed that he can barely live

52
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:09,400
because his mother figure is a prisoner.

53
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,640
I can't bear to see Na

54
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:28,880
in that condition.

55
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,640
I will end this problem

56
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:33,240
with my own life!

57
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,720
- No, Madam.
- Please don't!

58
00:05:34,800 --> 00:05:35,680
- No.
- Don't, Madam.

59
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:37,960
- Please don't.
- No, Madam.

60
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:40,880
This way, I won't trouble you again.

61
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:43,320
Take care of Na and Nee for me.

62
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:44,520
Don't do it.

63
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,840
This is not how you solve the problem.

64
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:47,920
No, Madam.

65
00:05:58,960 --> 00:05:59,840
Pin.

66
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:03,120
You must help her, Pin.

67
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:06,600
I'm begging you.

68
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:08,760
How am I supposed to help?

69
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:12,160
I can even bow to you if you want. Please.

70
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,000
Mom. Please don't.

71
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,440
If you bow to me, I'd end up in Hell.

72
00:06:16,520 --> 00:06:17,440
Mom.

73
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,160
- Mom.
- Un, that's enough.

74
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:21,120
Mom. Don't bow to me.

75
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:28,520
What do you want me to do

76
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,840
so you can be happy?

77
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:34,440
I'm at a loss for words.

78
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,280
Your mom is something.

79
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,840
Letting her daughter
take the fall for her madam?

80
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:45,640
You think Mr. Yai will let you off easily?

81
00:06:51,720 --> 00:06:54,440
I… I don't know.

82
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:55,840
Right now,

83
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:59,560
I just want to disappear from this world.

84
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,480
I don't want to know anything anymore.

85
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:19,120
So how long will Pin have to run for?

86
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,880
Why? Do you miss her?

87
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:23,960
It's not like that.

88
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:26,760
I'm just wondering that if Yai won't quit…

89
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:29,800
Then let him keep hunting her down.

90
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:32,480
I believe he has a soft spot for Pin.

91
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:35,160
And Pin wouldn't dare to upset her mom.

92
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:40,080
In the meantime, we find a way to have
Na marry Onsa-ang as soon as possible,

93
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:42,680
so we can use her father's power

94
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,240
to get rid of Yai.

95
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:49,040
You're as sharp as ever.

96
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:53,480
So… do you love me?

97
00:07:56,280 --> 00:07:58,520
Auntie! Auntie.

98
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,760
What is it now?

99
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,960
You always pick the worst time, huh?

100
00:08:04,040 --> 00:08:07,080
Is it true that
Pin stole our money and ran away?

101
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,520
The workers were gossiping
about it nonstop.

102
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,760
Yes.

103
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:15,960
I knew that deep down she was evil

104
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:18,040
but was acting timid and naive.

105
00:08:18,120 --> 00:08:19,720
Who would be as obviously evil as you?

106
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:23,080
Wait.

107
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:26,840
What is it now?

108
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:30,720
I'm gonna go outside,
since Pan's not here,

109
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,280
so I don't have to go train at the resort.

110
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:35,400
But you have to work for me.

111
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,480
Go take care of Onsa-ang.

112
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,480
We need her.

113
00:08:40,600 --> 00:08:41,720
5,000 per day.

114
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:44,200
You won't even get 500 baht

115
00:08:44,280 --> 00:08:46,360
if I don't see the results.

116
00:08:48,080 --> 00:08:49,680
A woman like me

117
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:52,600
won't just leech off of you for a living.

118
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:05,560
Hey.

119
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,600
Mr. Yai.

120
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,040
Mr. Yai.

121
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:15,640
Pan.

122
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:18,200
Go gather Madam Krongsuk
and everyone here now.

123
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:19,280
Yes, sir.

124
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:20,440
No need.

125
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:24,880
Mr. Yai. I was about to go see you.

126
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,080
Go stop Na and On.

127
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:30,320
Don't let them come down now.

128
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,480
Yes, ma'am.

129
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:35,000
- It's too late.
- Is breakfast ready?

130
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,800
Serve it to On upstairs.
She'll have it there.

131
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:42,240
You're really living
the high life, aren't you?

132
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:44,920
What's going on?

133
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:48,960
We checked the financial records

134
00:09:49,040 --> 00:09:50,760
and found that there are millions missing.

135
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,440
How will you take responsibility?

136
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,000
I wasn't being careful

137
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,800
and trusted Pin
to be the one to deposit the money.

138
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:04,360
Actually, I found that
some money was missing too,

139
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:06,040
so I already reported to Madam.

140
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:08,520
Pin would never do something like that.

141
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:11,360
I'll go find her, so we can talk it out.

142
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,760
Pin ran away.

143
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:14,400
She must fear the consequences.

144
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,440
Then if the culprit is missing,

145
00:10:17,640 --> 00:10:19,840
I'll just take it out on someone here.

146
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,360
Uh, Mr. Yai.

147
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:22,880
Pan, get the truck.

148
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:25,440
- What are you going to do to me?
- Let him go.

149
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:26,560
- Na's not a part of this!
- Come here!

150
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,480
Ow, Mr. Yai.

151
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:30,840
You can't do this! It's against the law.

152
00:10:30,920 --> 00:10:32,080
Hey. Help!

153
00:10:32,160 --> 00:10:33,520
I live by the honor among thieves.

154
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,400
Come here.

155
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,400
Hey! Don't do this, Mr. Yai!

156
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:40,120
Don't touch my nephew. Stop! Let Na go!

157
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:43,200
Teera!

158
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,200
Jerd! Kan!

159
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:48,360
Help Mr. Na.

160
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,240
Jerd, you idiot!

161
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,200
Are you trying to kill my nephew?

162
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:04,520
Enough, Auntie! Stop! It hurts.

163
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,480
Stop it, both of you.

164
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,560
Mr. Yai, let Na go.

165
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,120
Just tell me what you want.

166
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:12,720
Tell them to stand right there.

167
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,240
Both of you, go ahead.

168
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,000
Stand there.

169
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:26,680
Good night and sweet dreams.

170
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:31,400
Don't shoot!

171
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,800
What do you really want?!

172
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:35,600
If you want Na back,

173
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:38,680
give me the one who extorted the money
by tomorrow before sunset.

174
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:40,520
Are you talking about Pin?

175
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,520
I'm offering an easy way out.

176
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,320
This way, no one has to die.

177
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:49,280
Get up. Come here.

178
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:51,000
- Don't you dare.
- Na!

179
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:53,120
- Come here. Come.
- Auntie, help.

180
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,600
Go. Get in.

181
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:57,800
Na!

182
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,520
Don't follow us.

183
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:01,400
Na.

184
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,560
Auntie! Should we call the police?!

185
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:07,200
Are you crazy? You want them to kill Na?

186
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:09,280
Then what should we do?

187
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:33,000
Why don't we try reasoning
like civilized people do?

188
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,600
Why are you always violent?

189
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:37,720
Want me to act fake like you?

190
00:12:37,800 --> 00:12:38,920
I wouldn't know how to.

191
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:43,680
I'm an outlaw. Fighting is in my blood.

192
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:45,040
That's not true.

193
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:47,240
You've been violent since childhood,

194
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:48,760
and it became your…

195
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:51,600
nature.

196
00:12:54,760 --> 00:12:56,720
At least I'm better than a liar like you.

197
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:03,800
You pulled one hell of a stunt
at this shed.

198
00:13:04,480 --> 00:13:05,640
Don't you remember?

199
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:14,640
Help!

200
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:16,920
Is anyone out there?!

201
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,560
What happened, Yai?

202
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:27,560
- I was about to--
- He tried to burn me alive in this shed.

203
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,800
Why are you being like this?

204
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,920
Do you want to see me die from stress?!

205
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:36,600
You remember now?

206
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:38,720
Remember how much you hurt me?

207
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:42,160
A single sentence
was all it took to convince Uncle Paisal.

208
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,880
Didn't it even cross your mind?

209
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:46,200
You never did anything to gain his trust.

210
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:47,440
You did it all to yourself.

211
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:50,640
If I could turn back time,
I'd let you die in here!

212
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:54,920
Actually,
I later confessed to Uncle Paisal

213
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,240
that I was playing with fireworks,

214
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:58,240
and the fire started on its own.

215
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:01,440
He didn't believe me.

216
00:14:02,760 --> 00:14:05,760
He thought I was trying to help you.

217
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,480
You think I'll believe you?

218
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:15,120
You're so two-faced.

219
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,600
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai!

220
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,360
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai!

221
00:14:36,240 --> 00:14:39,280
<i>Pin. How are you doing?</i>

222
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:41,040
<i>Did you find a place to stay?</i>

223
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,480
<i>I'm so worried.</i>

224
00:14:43,920 --> 00:14:47,120
Un, tell me right now where Pin is.

225
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,800
You don't need to worry, Madam.

226
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,400
She's not going to come back.

227
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:52,960
She promised me.

228
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:55,440
Yai has taken Na hostage.

229
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:59,000
He's demanded Pin in exchange,
or he'll kill Tatsana.

230
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:01,720
Call Pin and tell her
to come back right now. Now!

231
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:02,880
Madam.

232
00:15:02,960 --> 00:15:05,280
But Yai thinks Pin stole his money.

233
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,720
If Pin came back,

234
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:08,440
he would hurt her for sure.

235
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:10,600
So you plan to be selfish

236
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:13,200
and let my nephew die, Un?!

237
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:14,960
I didn't mean it like that.

238
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:18,800
Pin?

239
00:15:18,880 --> 00:15:19,840
- Give it to me. I'll talk to her.
- Madam.

240
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:20,800
Please don't.

241
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:23,400
Madam. Yai wouldn't spare Pin, Madam.

242
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:24,280
- Let go.
- Wait.

243
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,560
Un. Are you betraying me?

244
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:33,360
Pin. Mr. Yai took Mr. Na.

245
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:35,560
He threatened to kill Mr. Na

246
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,120
if you don't return.

247
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:39,280
Come back right now.

248
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:43,640
Secure it.

249
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,280
Wasn't that too much?

250
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:56,280
It'd be hard to use her now.

251
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:57,360
You need to keep calm.

252
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,600
I don't care if anyone dies. Screw them!

253
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:02,040
But Na has to survive.

254
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:04,440
Lock her up.

255
00:16:04,520 --> 00:16:05,920
Don't let her find a way to contact Pin.

256
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,320
- I didn't see her.
- Me either.

257
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:23,000
- Piak. How was it?
- Didn't find her.

258
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:24,400
No sign of her at all.

259
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:26,920
No need to keep looking.

260
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,160
She called me.

261
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:29,840
And where's Pin right now?

262
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:37,000
Hey, I said no need to call
or look for her anymore.

263
00:16:37,080 --> 00:16:40,240
Pin's coming back
because Aunt Un texted her,

264
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:42,160
saying Mr. Yai took Mr. Na

265
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:44,400
and threatened to kill him
if Pin doesn't return.

266
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:46,560
- Huh? Really?
- Yeah.

267
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:00,680
Thank you.

268
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:12,079
Mr. Yai, I'm back.

269
00:17:12,160 --> 00:17:13,839
Where do you want me to meet you?

270
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:17,040
I'll hurry there.

271
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:19,480
Please don't do anything to Mr. Na.

272
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:38,720
Pin is coming. You can go now.

273
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:42,960
Once this game ends, you should just
drag all of them to prison.

274
00:17:43,040 --> 00:17:45,880
So I can shift back
to being a normal human being.

275
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:46,760
Yeah, yeah.

276
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:48,560
Just leave the truck with me and leave.

277
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,240
Fire!

278
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,680
Fire! Fire!

279
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,520
Fire! Help!

280
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:42,760
Help! Anyone!

281
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:44,480
Anybody, help!

282
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:56,560
<i>What happened, Yai?</i>

283
00:18:57,200 --> 00:19:00,680
- I was about to--
- He tried to burn me alive in this shed.

284
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:36,880
Mr. Na…

285
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:40,760
You're too late, Pinanong.

286
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:46,120
I was tired of waiting,
so I burnt him alive,

287
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:48,680
taking revenge for you in one go.

288
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:51,800
Taking revenge?

289
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:55,160
Yeah. Because he cheated on you.

290
00:19:58,520 --> 00:19:59,440
Hold on.

291
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:03,400
You should at least thank me once
before running to see his body.

292
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,640
How could you do that?

293
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,240
How could you kill someone in cold blood?

294
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:11,520
It's a major sin.

295
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:13,960
He also committed a sin by exploiting you.

296
00:20:14,040 --> 00:20:15,400
And you extorting my money is also a sin.

297
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:17,080
Madam's using you is a sin too.

298
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,920
Your mom helping the wicked is also a sin.

299
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,000
We're all sinful.

300
00:20:20,080 --> 00:20:21,520
Let's just share it, so it's fair.

301
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,920
You're misunderstanding.

302
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,320
Mr. Na has never fooled me.

303
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:30,480
We weren't dating,
so he can love whoever he wants.

304
00:20:30,560 --> 00:20:32,360
Why did you have to take his life?

305
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:36,080
Who would have known
that you're not upset with him?

306
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,320
But he's dead anyway.

307
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:43,200
I've got an idea. You can have his body.

308
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:46,560
You can hug him all night if you want.

309
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:55,160
I never believed you were truly evil,

310
00:20:57,040 --> 00:20:58,560
but now,

311
00:20:58,640 --> 00:21:00,360
I'm sure you are.

312
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,600
Pinanong.

313
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:04,560
- Pinanong.
- Let go of me. I'll go see Mr. Na.

314
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:06,840
He might still be alive.

315
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:07,960
Mr. Na.

316
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:10,000
- I'll go see Mr. Na.
- Come here.

317
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:11,000
Let go!

318
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:14,760
- You wanted to catch me, didn't you?
- Come here.

319
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:15,880
Well, here I am.

320
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:17,560
Why did you have to kill Mr. Na?

321
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:19,680
Huh? Why don't you just kill me?

322
00:21:19,760 --> 00:21:22,520
Why don't you kill me too? Kill me.

323
00:21:22,600 --> 00:21:24,080
- Kill me.
- Pin.

324
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:29,560
Mr. Na?

325
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:31,560
Mr. Na.

326
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:40,200
Didn't you say Mr. Na was dead?

327
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:49,160
Mr. Yai! Help me!

328
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,120
I don't want to die!

329
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,600
Mr. Yai, there's a fire! Help!

330
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:53,120
Mr. Yai! Help me!

331
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:02,880
Help…

332
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:08,880
Na.

333
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:12,800
Na!

334
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:14,720
Damn it.

335
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:34,680
Ask your sweetheart yourself

336
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:37,520
why he set himself on fire.

337
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,400
Or were you trying to blame me again?

338
00:22:45,720 --> 00:22:47,960
Well, it was an accident.

339
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:50,480
I tipped over the lantern,

340
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,640
which caused the flames to spread.

341
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:57,360
I'm so glad to see you back.

342
00:22:58,200 --> 00:22:59,640
Since the day you ran away,

343
00:22:59,720 --> 00:23:02,080
not a moment has been easy for me.

344
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,200
I was worried.

345
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,800
I was worried about how you were living,

346
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:09,600
what you were eating,
or where you were staying.

347
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:15,080
I've put you through this trouble.

348
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:17,440
I'm so sorry.

349
00:23:23,560 --> 00:23:24,560
Damn it.

350
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:26,280
Protect yourself, will you?

351
00:23:26,920 --> 00:23:28,400
This guy already has a girlfriend.

352
00:23:30,960 --> 00:23:32,640
Can you let Mr. Na go now?

353
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:36,240
I hope you'll do as you said you would.

354
00:23:38,800 --> 00:23:41,720
Fine. Suit yourself.

355
00:23:48,120 --> 00:23:49,280
Wait.

356
00:23:53,720 --> 00:23:54,920
What do you want now?

357
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:57,600
Someone has to pay

358
00:23:57,680 --> 00:23:59,000
for the farm's stolen money.

359
00:23:59,520 --> 00:24:02,280
Pan has prepared a torture device.

360
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:04,680
One has to stay and face punishment,

361
00:24:04,760 --> 00:24:06,480
and one will walk free.

362
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:08,160
That's breaking your promise.

363
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:10,520
You told Mom that if I came to see you,

364
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:12,880
you would let Mr. Na go.

365
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:14,800
I'm right here.

366
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:17,040
Just put me in prison and let Mr. Na go.

367
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:19,520
It wouldn't be fun
if I let him go so easily.

368
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:23,000
There should be a little game
to make it exciting.

369
00:24:23,080 --> 00:24:24,120
I'll give you a choice.

370
00:24:24,200 --> 00:24:26,800
If you choose to go, Pin will stay.

371
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:30,680
Or you will have to sacrifice yourself

372
00:24:30,760 --> 00:24:31,880
and let Pinanong go.

373
00:24:46,760 --> 00:24:47,920
Well?

374
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,440
You're taking a lot of time.

375
00:24:49,520 --> 00:24:51,880
I might change my mind, bro.

376
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:02,320
Pin.

377
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:06,280
I'm sorry.

378
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:34,280
<i>Take good care of our Indian cork tree.</i>

379
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,800
I'll wait for only you, Mr. Na.

380
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:43,160
Well, how was your beloved angel?

381
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:45,680
Running away without looking back.

382
00:25:46,560 --> 00:25:49,320
I thought he was gonna take
more time to think.

383
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:57,800
I hope you've grown wiser by now.

384
00:25:57,880 --> 00:26:00,040
The nephew has been exposed.

385
00:26:00,120 --> 00:26:03,720
Now, it's time to expose the mastermind.

386
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:04,720
Come on.

387
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:08,800
Let's expose that madam
who made you take the fall for her.

388
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:10,240
I'm not going.

389
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:14,120
You must go. Go open your mother's eyes.

390
00:26:14,200 --> 00:26:16,360
Make her realize
her medical bills were paid by me,

391
00:26:16,440 --> 00:26:19,000
not that witch.

392
00:26:19,080 --> 00:26:21,320
Help her see
through that foolish, blind loyalty.

393
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:24,560
If I do it,

394
00:26:25,360 --> 00:26:27,120
you'll feel better

395
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:30,560
and stop stressing or overthinking, right?

396
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,480
Yes.

397
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:36,120
I swear I will never betray Madam.

398
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,600
If you break your oath,

399
00:26:39,840 --> 00:26:41,320
may I die a painful death.

400
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:42,440
No.

401
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:44,840
I won't do it.

402
00:26:44,920 --> 00:26:48,800
Even if you kill me, I won't do it.

403
00:26:53,280 --> 00:26:56,000
You're unbelievable.

404
00:26:57,720 --> 00:26:59,000
Fine.

405
00:27:00,040 --> 00:27:01,640
If you want to die so much, then come.

406
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:31,200
Where did everyone in this house go?

407
00:27:31,280 --> 00:27:33,200
No one's preparing dinner?

408
00:27:34,080 --> 00:27:35,200
And what is this?

409
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:38,400
Low-quality kitchenware.

410
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:41,040
Let's take a look in here.

411
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:51,720
It's expiring tomorrow?

412
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:57,440
This one too.

413
00:27:57,960 --> 00:28:00,440
Auntie! What are you doing?!

414
00:28:00,520 --> 00:28:01,840
Who is your auntie?

415
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,240
Do not call me that.

416
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:05,120
Call me Ms. Jan.

417
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:08,080
I'm not your family.

418
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:10,160
Auntie! Oh--

419
00:28:10,240 --> 00:28:11,480
Ms. Jan.

420
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:13,840
Why are you throwing away my stuff?

421
00:28:15,880 --> 00:28:19,720
I planned to serve these
for dinner this evening.

422
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:24,280
Perhaps this household
eats only junk food.

423
00:28:24,360 --> 00:28:27,520
That's why they lack the nutrition
to develop their brains.

424
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:29,720
You can skip dinner if you wish,

425
00:28:29,800 --> 00:28:32,200
because both Aunt Un and Pin
are not here today.

426
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:34,640
And I can only make omelets.

427
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:35,560
You want one?

428
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:37,080
Stop right there.

429
00:28:37,160 --> 00:28:39,240
Miss On doesn't like omelets,

430
00:28:39,840 --> 00:28:41,160
because they're oily.

431
00:28:43,000 --> 00:28:44,080
Then she can skip dinner.

432
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:46,800
Just use this time to pray
that Mr. Na survives…

433
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:49,080
What happened to Mr. Na?

434
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:51,800
Huh?

435
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:55,680
Please don't go down now.

436
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:57,200
There's no one downstairs.

437
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:59,360
Na is also still at the farm.

438
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:00,840
Then I'll go look at the farm.

439
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,440
You can't go there.

440
00:29:02,520 --> 00:29:04,520
The farm's very, very hot.

441
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:08,200
I think you should
take a shower to cool down one more time.

442
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:09,560
Come on. Let's have a spa day.

443
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:12,640
- I'll get the water ready.
- Miss. Miss.

444
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:14,320
Mr. Na is in trouble.

445
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:31,480
Hey.

446
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:33,000
What do you want?

447
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:36,960
Where did your boss take Mr. Na?

448
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:38,800
I have no idea.

449
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:41,160
Where the hell is my gun?

450
00:29:42,840 --> 00:29:43,880
Come at me if you dare.

451
00:29:44,760 --> 00:29:48,000
Consider yourself lucky I didn't break
your arms and legs last time.

452
00:29:49,280 --> 00:29:50,440
Hey.

453
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,480
‪-Get off me!
‪-I won't let go!

454
00:30:14,560 --> 00:30:16,840
- Let go of me!
- I won't.

455
00:30:25,680 --> 00:30:26,840
Are you ganging up on me?

456
00:30:27,560 --> 00:30:29,520
You're not a real tough guy, are you?

457
00:30:30,440 --> 00:30:31,760
What's going on here?

458
00:30:31,840 --> 00:30:34,840
Mr. Yai took Mr. Na hostage
and demanded that Pin go meet him.

459
00:30:34,920 --> 00:30:36,680
I'm grilling him for information.

460
00:30:39,840 --> 00:30:42,000
Call a ride for me, Jan.

461
00:30:42,080 --> 00:30:43,920
I'm going to the police station.

462
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:47,400
If the police can't find Na,
I'll have Dad fire them all.

463
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:48,520
Yes, Miss.

464
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:50,640
Where are you going?

465
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:58,240
I tried to stop her,
but she wouldn't listen.

466
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:00,640
I don't know what to do anymore.

467
00:31:01,440 --> 00:31:05,520
Why didn't you tell me
that the madman had taken Na?

468
00:31:05,600 --> 00:31:06,720
Wait.

469
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,160
Just calm down, On.

470
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:10,240
I'm trying to find a way to help Na.

471
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:12,160
This is a matter of life and death.

472
00:31:12,240 --> 00:31:13,920
Who could possibly stay calm?

473
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:16,680
You're wealthy,
yet you have zero leverage.

474
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:19,200
That's why you're petrified of him. Move.

475
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:21,280
I said you can't go!

476
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:28,920
Well…

477
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:33,000
Mr. Yai threatened

478
00:31:33,080 --> 00:31:34,480
that if we called the police,

479
00:31:35,080 --> 00:31:36,360
he'll kill Na.

480
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:42,240
I didn't tell you
because I was worried you'd panic.

481
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:46,320
Mr. Yai is far more cruel
than what you've seen.

482
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:50,040
That's true, sis.

483
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:52,680
He has killed, robbed,

484
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:55,280
and raped countless people.

485
00:31:56,120 --> 00:31:57,120
That's enough.

486
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:03,360
And Mr. Yai took Na hostage

487
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:06,640
because we discovered that Pin
had been siphoning funds from the farm.

488
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:09,240
So Mr. Yai wants Pin in exchange for Na.

489
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:13,360
I've sent Pin to him now.

490
00:32:13,440 --> 00:32:14,840
All we can do is wait.

491
00:32:15,760 --> 00:32:17,040
But he's a criminal.

492
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:18,960
He might break his word.

493
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:21,440
I don't want to wait anymore, Auntie.

494
00:32:22,080 --> 00:32:24,040
I fear something might happen to Na.

495
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:27,160
- On.
- Na?

496
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:28,360
Na.

497
00:32:32,920 --> 00:32:36,440
I waited in the back area of the farm
and saw Mr. Na walk out alone.

498
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:39,880
Are you okay, Na?

499
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:42,080
I can't live without you.

500
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:48,440
I thought I wouldn't make it either.

501
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:50,600
I missed you so much, On.

502
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:58,120
Another one
of your biggest fans is waiting.

503
00:33:01,840 --> 00:33:03,160
Auntie.

504
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:09,760
Did Yai do anything to you?

505
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:12,760
He almost did.

506
00:33:13,520 --> 00:33:15,880
Mr. Yai was trying to burn me alive,

507
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,880
but Pin arrived in time.

508
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:19,600
From now on,

509
00:33:19,680 --> 00:33:22,720
I won't let anyone hurt you, Na.

510
00:33:26,680 --> 00:33:29,480
Mr. Yai. You can shoot me anywhere.

511
00:33:29,560 --> 00:33:31,640
Why did you have to take me this far?

512
00:33:40,280 --> 00:33:41,440
Where exactly are we?

513
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,120
It's beautiful, isn't it?

514
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:45,920
It's not heaven, just a stopover.

515
00:33:49,080 --> 00:33:50,600
I'm exhausted.

516
00:33:50,680 --> 00:33:52,480
I don't want to go anywhere else.

517
00:33:52,560 --> 00:33:54,320
Please just let me die here.

518
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:56,080
I thought you were worried about your mom

519
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:57,280
and didn't want to die.

520
00:33:57,360 --> 00:33:58,920
Why are you giving up so easily?

521
00:33:59,520 --> 00:34:03,000
Maybe without a stupid daughter like me,

522
00:34:03,800 --> 00:34:06,320
Mom would be happier.

523
00:34:07,280 --> 00:34:10,600
My being a burden to her has forced her

524
00:34:10,679 --> 00:34:14,360
into a difficult life,
having to serve Madam to this day.

525
00:34:14,440 --> 00:34:18,520
Pinanong, do you realize
how messed up your logic is?

526
00:34:19,480 --> 00:34:21,400
I'm going insane. Why do I have to…

527
00:34:22,520 --> 00:34:24,520
get involved with a stupid girl like you?

528
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:54,440
Pin.

529
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:58,720
Run, Pin. Now. Pin!

530
00:34:58,800 --> 00:34:59,760
Run.

531
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:04,000
Hurry, Pin.

532
00:35:04,840 --> 00:35:05,880
Faster.

533
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:35,440
Are you sure you won't screw up again?

534
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:37,920
This time, I reached out
to a den of hired guns

535
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:40,080
and told them to closely follow Yai.

536
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:42,800
There's no chance he'll survive.

537
00:35:45,160 --> 00:35:46,720
You can't let any of them make it.

538
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:49,320
Both of them must not survive.

539
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:52,200
Pin too, Krong?

540
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:54,000
Why?

541
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:55,760
I don't trust her.

542
00:35:56,920 --> 00:35:59,880
I'm sure she's switched to Yai's side.

543
00:36:01,120 --> 00:36:03,080
We need to nip this in the bud.

544
00:36:08,240 --> 00:36:09,760
Get down. Get down.

545
00:36:13,840 --> 00:36:15,640
Why are they chasing us?

546
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:16,560
Are they drunk?

547
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:19,560
Drunk? They're clearly trying to kill us.

548
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:24,040
Hey, what are you doing?

549
00:36:24,120 --> 00:36:25,480
I'm not in the mood right now.

550
00:36:26,080 --> 00:36:28,800
A gun. Don't you always carry one?

551
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:32,200
It's in the truck.

552
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:39,640
What are we going to do?

553
00:36:57,480 --> 00:36:58,600
Go look over there.

554
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:11,520
Uncle Pload taught me

555
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:15,160
that when the dog barks, you must
stay still and wait for the strike.

556
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:23,520
Bastard. You're dead!

557
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:29,800
<i>Pin.</i>

558
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:31,560
<i>I'm sorry I couldn't protect you.</i>

559
00:38:43,800 --> 00:38:45,440
I never hated you, Mr. Yai.

560
00:39:16,720 --> 00:39:17,680
I'm okay.

561
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:40,080
Pin?

562
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:45,920
Manager, where's Pin? Has she come back?

563
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:48,280
Not yet. But Mr. Na's back.

564
00:39:50,000 --> 00:39:53,160
That means Yai has Pin now.

565
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:55,600
So where did he take her now?

566
00:39:55,680 --> 00:39:57,280
I'll trade my life for hers.

567
00:39:58,800 --> 00:40:00,000
Calm down, Aunt Un.

568
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:02,640
Madam has planned

569
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:04,240
that once we have Mr. Na back,

570
00:40:04,320 --> 00:40:06,440
we'll send someone
to rescue Pin right away.

571
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:09,280
We'll get Pin home safely in no time.

572
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:10,920
Is that true?

573
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:15,680
I knew it. Madam would never abandon Pin.

574
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:17,160
Yes.

575
00:40:17,240 --> 00:40:18,880
Madam loves her so much.

576
00:40:18,960 --> 00:40:20,400
She would never abandon her.

577
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:31,680
Why are you stopping? Keep walking.

578
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:33,960
The path is dark.

579
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:35,840
I don't remember which way to go.

580
00:40:35,920 --> 00:40:39,320
I think you're just getting us lost
to stall for time.

581
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:42,320
Hey, are you tricking us?

582
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:47,560
Yai told me that
he took Tatsana around here, really.

583
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:49,360
He might have moved somewhere else.

584
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:50,920
Moved somewhere else?

585
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:52,000
- Moved somewhere else?!
- Hey.

586
00:40:52,080 --> 00:40:53,520
Stop right there.

587
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:55,840
Assaulting someone
won't end with just a fine.

588
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:56,760
You'd end up in court.

589
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:59,240
You seem to know your way around the law.

590
00:41:02,120 --> 00:41:02,960
So what?

591
00:41:03,680 --> 00:41:05,560
Thieves have to know the law too.

592
00:41:07,720 --> 00:41:09,840
You even brought a law book with you?

593
00:41:11,320 --> 00:41:14,360
Just tell me who you really are.

594
00:41:15,560 --> 00:41:16,440
What are you talking about?

595
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:17,360
I don't understand.

596
00:41:17,440 --> 00:41:20,400
I suspect this guy
isn't just a regular thief.

597
00:41:24,720 --> 00:41:25,960
- Hey!
- Hey.

598
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,440
- Pan, get back here!
- Go after him.

599
00:41:27,520 --> 00:41:28,480
Hey.

600
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:31,400
- Stop!
- Let go.

601
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:36,320
For the stubborn ones,
you need to use an elephant tranquilizer.

602
00:41:36,400 --> 00:41:37,720
What are you doing?

603
00:41:37,800 --> 00:41:39,160
Don't do this. No.

604
00:41:39,240 --> 00:41:42,680
Help! Help me! Help!

605
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:44,160
Quiet.

606
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:46,480
Okay, okay. I give up.

607
00:41:46,560 --> 00:41:47,640
I'll tell you.

608
00:42:50,840 --> 00:42:52,440
Wow, nice shot, Chief.

609
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:53,760
How did you get here?

610
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:56,840
Let's get to my house. It's not safe here.

611
00:42:57,760 --> 00:42:58,600
Yes.

612
00:43:02,520 --> 00:43:04,720
Pin, we survived.

613
00:43:04,800 --> 00:43:06,600
This is Village Chief Yam's territory.

614
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:08,480
Come.

615
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:15,040
Good thing my informant told me strangers
had trespassed into the area.

616
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:16,840
Otherwise, you'd have ended up dead.

617
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:24,680
Pin, go hide in the room.

618
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:26,080
They might have followed us here.

619
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:35,800
Where did Mr. Yai go?

620
00:43:44,960 --> 00:43:46,200
Mr. Yai?

621
00:44:01,960 --> 00:44:03,520
Hey. Who's that?

622
00:44:05,320 --> 00:44:07,920
Sneak around like that,
and I'll shoot your guts out.

623
00:44:09,360 --> 00:44:11,240
No, don't shoot.

624
00:44:11,320 --> 00:44:14,360
It's… It's me, Mr. Yai.

625
00:44:15,760 --> 00:44:17,680
Oh, I thought it was someone else.

626
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:21,440
If you want to peep while I bathe,
just do it. I'm not shy.

627
00:44:21,520 --> 00:44:24,320
Feel free to caress my six-pack
with your eyes.

628
00:44:24,400 --> 00:44:25,480
It's not what you think.

629
00:44:25,560 --> 00:44:28,600
I just saw that your shirt was torn,

630
00:44:28,680 --> 00:44:30,120
so I was looking for you.

631
00:44:30,200 --> 00:44:32,600
I thought someone had hurt you.

632
00:44:34,760 --> 00:44:37,760
I was on night watch last night,
and a nail tore my shirt.

633
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:41,520
Well, since you're already here,
can you hand me the towel?

634
00:44:50,880 --> 00:44:52,040
It's right there.

635
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:56,520
Where is it?

636
00:44:57,200 --> 00:44:58,840
How are you gonna find it
if you don't look?

637
00:45:02,960 --> 00:45:03,800
‪Pin.

638
00:45:05,240 --> 00:45:07,120
Clumsy as ever. Let me see.

639
00:45:07,200 --> 00:45:09,000
Did your head split open?

640
00:45:09,080 --> 00:45:10,360
I'm okay.

641
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:13,800
How are you okay? Just let me see.

642
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:17,640
It's red.

643
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:25,280
Heal up. Poof.

644
00:45:35,360 --> 00:45:36,840
You can let go of me now.

645
00:45:54,920 --> 00:45:56,480
That's my head, not a nail, you know?

646
00:45:56,560 --> 00:45:57,480
Chief.

647
00:45:57,560 --> 00:45:59,960
Your head is full of nothing
but ways to take advantage of her.

648
00:46:01,440 --> 00:46:03,320
I just had to knock some sense into it.

649
00:46:03,400 --> 00:46:06,320
Take advantage? This is my woman.

650
00:46:09,760 --> 00:46:13,480
Even if that's true, you can't do
something obscene out here.

651
00:46:13,560 --> 00:46:14,720
Get out of here.

652
00:46:14,800 --> 00:46:16,120
Don't just stand there.

653
00:46:17,640 --> 00:46:19,240
That's all you have?

654
00:46:19,800 --> 00:46:21,440
And you're still showing it off?

655
00:46:21,520 --> 00:46:22,760
Leave, right now.

656
00:46:23,680 --> 00:46:26,600
Insulting me like this… If I didn't
respect you, things would get ugly.

657
00:46:26,680 --> 00:46:28,000
Go ahead.

658
00:46:28,080 --> 00:46:29,600
I'm leaving.

659
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:40,360
Then I might have to show you how
ruthless and insatiable Bandit Yai can be.

660
00:46:40,440 --> 00:46:42,440
We're not going to sleep tonight, Pin.

661
00:46:42,520 --> 00:46:44,280
Win, shoot his leg.

662
00:46:44,360 --> 00:46:45,280
Sorry, Manager.

663
00:46:45,360 --> 00:46:46,480
- I must follow orders.
- Hey.

664
00:46:46,560 --> 00:46:47,520
Get all the weapons ready.

665
00:46:47,600 --> 00:46:49,920
<i>I will take Paisal Farm.</i>

666
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:52,600
All this vengeance will be settled today.

667
00:46:52,680 --> 00:46:55,040
I will marry Pinanong.

668
00:46:55,120 --> 00:46:57,320
- Huh?
- I'm willing to marry him.

669
00:46:58,440 --> 00:46:59,600
Pin…

670
00:47:41,040 --> 00:47:43,280
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
